      "side": 1,
      "message": "I tried both your suggestions but then redacted them.\n\n- I didn\u0027t move the function to its own file because there\u0027s a little leakage of GA specific stuff in androidMetrics_uploadMetrics already (the URL to post to in debug/prod mode). I\u0027d have to move that as well, and it seemed like an overkill.\n  - That said, we want to eventually also ping code.google.com in parallel. I\u0027ll hide away the backend specific formatting of post data at that point.\n- I didn\u0027t add a unittest just for the post function because it seems too low level to me. All this does is create a formatted string. A unittest for this function would be extremely brittle -- every change in code needs a corresponding change in unittest.\nhttps://sites.google.com/a/google.com/tater-tott/posts/2013/09/episode_299__test_behavior__not_implementation",
